
[1]intrust

   INTRUST', v.t. [in and trust.] To deliver in trust; to confide to the
   care of; to commit to another with confidence in his fidelity; as, to
   intrust a servant with one's money or goods, or to intrust money or
   goods to a servant. We intrust an agent or factor with commercial
   business, or we intrust commercial concerns to an agent.

   We intrust our friends with secrets, or intrust secrets to them.
